1. Create Spring Boot Project
2. GetMapping and PostMapping - Test in browser and PostMan
3. Add "springfox-boot-starter" dependency
4. Enable Swagger dcocumentation in spring application - "@EnableSwagger2"
5. Run the application - "http://localhost:9000/swagger-ui/"
 you can see controller and error controller (we havent designed)
6. Update/customize the api documentation - create configuration file

<!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/io.springfox/springfox-boot-starter -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
    <artifactId>springfox-boot-starter</artifactId>
    <version>3.0.0</version>
</dependency>

This dependency autowires whatever is necessary